```json
{
  "type": "metric",
  "title": "Example — minimal",
  "metrics": [
    { "label": "Bugs Resolved",  "value": 34 },
    { "label": "Backlog Size",   "value": 47 },
    { "label": "Avg Age at Fix", "value": "42 days" },
    { "label": "PRs Reviewed",   "value": 23 }
  ]
}
```

Only `label` and `value` are required. `value` accepts any string or number — include units inline when useful.

The new rate limiter uses a sliding window backed by Redis:

```typescript
async function checkRateLimit(key: string, limit: number, windowMs: number) {
  const now = Date.now();
  const windowStart = now - windowMs;

  await redis.zremrangebyscore(key, 0, windowStart);
  const count = await redis.zcard(key);

  if (count >= limit) throw new RateLimitError();

  await redis.zadd(key, now, `${now}`);
  await redis.pexpire(key, windowMs);
}
```

