Only `name` and `username` are required. Show only the columns that matter for your team.

```json
{
  "type": "chart",
  "title": "Error Rate Over Sprint",
  "chartType": "line",
  "xAxisLabel": "Day",
  "yAxisLabel": "Errors/hr",
  "series": [
    {
      "name": "Error Rate",
      "color": "#dc2626",
      "data": [
        { "x": "Mar 10", "y": 12.4 },
        { "x": "Mar 12", "y": 9.8 },
        { "x": "Mar 14", "y": 6.2 }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

`chartType` is `line`, `area`, or `bar`. `color` is optional — omit to use the default theme color. `xAxisLabel` and `yAxisLabel` are optional.

```json
{
  "type": "chart",
  "chartType": "area",
  "series": [
    {
      "name": "P50",
      "color": "#2563eb",
      "data": [ { "x": "Mar 10", "y": 42 }, { "x": "Mar 12", "y": 38 } ]
    },
    {
      "name": "P95",
      "color": "#9333ea",
      "data": [ { "x": "Mar 10", "y": 115 }, { "x": "Mar 12", "y": 98 } ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Add multiple objects to `series` for a multi-series chart. Each series gets its own color and legend entry.

```json
{
  "type": "chart",
  "chartType": "bar",
  "xAxisLabel": "Requests/sec",
  "yAxisLabel": "Latency (ms)",
  "series": [
    { "name": "P50", "color": "#2563eb", "data": [ { "x": "100", "y": 12 }, { "x": "5000", "y": 38 } ] },
    { "name": "P99", "color": "#dc2626", "data": [ { "x": "100", "y": 28 }, { "x": "5000", "y": 185 } ] }
  ]
}
```

Bar charts work well for comparisons across discrete categories. The `x` value in each data point can be a string (category label) or number.
